@JamesChooWK The Extras.txt is documented here: https://dev.px4.io/master/en/concept/system_startup.html#customizing-the-system-startup

It is used for system startup customisations - basically you're adding the mixer at runtime rather than as part of the firmware build. This is much easier for examples, testing,  and when you're doing something that only applies to your setup. 

You can copy the files onto the card using whatever mechanism you like - ie File explorer on windows. The files need to be present on the SD card before booting PX4. Again, they are not part of firmware, but are loaded as though they were.

@JamesChooWK So the point of the PR is that the message doesn't work on PX4 right now (as far as I know - I'm guessing based on what I see here).
So yes, you will have to build PX4 firmware with the changes in this code and upload it as "custom firmware". There are conflicts between the changes and master branch, so you might need to do some coding to integrate them.

Also note this PR did not get accepted yet - so there is no guarantee that even if you do this it will work.

@KeyneZzz Is this an extended fixed wing/vtol fix for https://github.com/PX4/Firmware/pull/10291?

> better to use yaw_sp than to ues yawspeed_sp?

For holding the heading it's better to have a constant yaw setpoint because a yawspeed setpoint can in principle drift.

